Camco Rises in London After Boosting Number of Carbon Credits

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-04-18T07:13:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/camco-rises-in-london-after-boosting-number-of-carbon-credits.html
Camco International Ltd. (CAO)  rose 4.3
percent to the highest price since June 2010 in London trading
after saying it increased its number of expected carbon credits
by 3 percent since September.  The shares advanced 0.75 pence to 18.25 pence, valuing the
company at 34.5 million pounds ($56 million), after the company
said in a statment today that its emission credits are estimated
at almost 27 million metric tons by the end of 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mathew Carr in London at 
